    {
      "label": {
        "none": [
          "Historical Context"
        ]
      },
      "value": {
        "none": [
          "The Apollo Space Program was proposed during the Cold War as a means to demonstrate technological superiority and achieve a significant milestone in human exploration. While there were some concerns about the environmental impact of rocket launches, these were largely addressed, and the program proceeded with strong public support. Ultimately, the Apollo missions successfully landed humans on the Moon, fulfilling their ambitious goals and marking a historic achievement in space exploration."
        ]
      }
    },
